race.comment: BELLMAN (1) was an impressive winner last time over 1800m at Wagga Riverside. Drops back in trip but is full of confidence and gets an important claim. Can win again. LOVEOFMYLIFE (4) scored last start at Lockhart to make it three wins from five starts this campaign. Draws to get the gun run and doesn't need to improve much to be involved again. CUMBRIAN QUEEN (7) battled away soundly into a midfield finish when resuming at Jerilderie. The subsequent form has been solid and she will appreciate the added trip. CABLE DE VEGA (8) next best. Has been freshened since some one paced efforts over further.
